avel and can nearly instantly transport ships from one gate to the next. If there is only one gate and no receiving gate, the sling tends to be very inaccurate. When arriving at a new system without a gate, a vessel may have to travel quite a large distan
ce to arrive at the intended destination.
\par 
\par The {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Union{\*\xmlclose}
 can now produce its own capital ships (carriers and battleships). These ships are not only completely self sustaining, (able to repair other vessels and produce fuel for a whole carrier group), but are also equipped with the first \'93Sling Drives\'94
 to propel them great distances instantly. Other command vessels must first travel to an existing Sling Gate.  The Sling Drives are still inaccurate and not as long ranged as the full sized Sling Gates, but are
 a great advantage over Warp Drives.  Now, Carrier Groups can freely move about the Fringe without the need to stay near a star base for fuel and support.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\insrsid6230726 While great leaps in technology and travel are made, tensions rise throughout the Fringe.  While under attack from the Republic, the entire {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Union{\*\xmlclose}
 was placed in a state of martial law. The Brave {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Union{\*\xmlclose} that had won its freedom from the Republic now strong-arms its own citizens in much the same way the Republic did. Based on proud military traditi
on, The {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Union{\*\xmlclose} has a tendency to treat non-military personnel as second class. Recently a bill was passed in parliament that allowed only military servicemen and war veterans to vote in elections.}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\cf17\insrsid6230726 .}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6230726 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\insrsid6230726 
\par While this puts a halt to what are considered \'93middle management\'94
 professions that drag down Union society, (namely Career Politicians and Lawyers) it disenfranchises trained engineers and shipbuilding professionals as well as other loyal citizens in non-military careers. While they are not military personne
l, they feel they are an essential part of Union society.
\par 
\par The Colonial ship builders start to withhold technology and slow ship production. A Union blockade of Colonial systems ensues, effectively halting needed supplies not just for ship construction, bu
t for food, medical supplies, and other and life sustaining needs as well. 
\par 
\par In retaliation, the Colonial forces launch new generation fighters and use them in terrorist style raids against Union blockade vessels. It is immediately apparent that these figh
ters are an extreme step above previous generation fighters. These fighters are faster and more agile than any fighter previously seen and are deadly effective at carrying out gorilla assault missions.
\par 
\par Union leaders are astonished. How is it possible that these fighters were developed without the knowledge of the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Union{\*\xmlclose}
 and under such extreme conditions? Why were such great advances withheld, and for how long?
\par 
\par The scientific community is also hard hit by this rift in the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Union{\*\xmlclose}. They are also unable to vote, but now fall under scrutiny of honest military personnel.  They sometimes fall prey to attack from the 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Union{\*\xmlclose}, for their indecision, and also suffer terrorist strikes from Colonial forces, for their support of Union oppression. Reluctantly they start to militarize their own forces under their banner of 
\'93The Federation.\'94
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cf2\insrsid6230726 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6230726 Here is where we also finally convert the game into a full Role Playing Game.  The full RPG expansion will allow players to earn credits in other methods rather than just co
mpleting missions.  These additional credits can be used to finally purchase, enhance, and command CAPITAL ships, including Carriers and Battleships.  Carriers can spawn and repair multiple command ships.  \'93Sling Gates\'94 and \'93Sling Drives\'94
 allow players to traverse the Fringe faster than ever before and open up new areas of space that were previously unreachable.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cf2\insrsid6230726 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6230726  Players in the game at this time will be called upon to carry out different missions depending on where they are based. Those based in Uni
on territories will be called upon to subvert rebellions and may be active participants in Union blockades of the Colonials.
\par 
\par Players based in Colonial space will be called upon to attack Union government ships.  Players in Federation space may need to def
end against attacks from both sides.  Players can change loyalties and mission by changing their base of operations to one of the three primary territories.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\ul\insrsid6230726 Occupations
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6230726 There is no denying it; some people just enjoy earning credits and building a bigger f
leet.  These players may earn credits by learning certain engineering and repair skills and opening up shop.  The number of skills they have and the size of their shop will dictate the traffic they can drive to their shop.  We will purposefully cause PC
\rquote s and NPC\rquote 
s to need the services of engineers and mechanics to upgrade and repair their ships.  At first, low level engineers and mechanics will be able to set up shop on a Carrier or Miramar Space station with its defensive networks to protect it from pirat
es and enemy factions (for a price of course).  Players will eventually want to move out and design their own mini-space stations or carrier groups with their own defensive network.  Colonials are particularly adept in ship building operations, but other 
factions may bring their own specialties to bear.
\par 
\par Another occupation players have available to them is mining.  Low level players can mine, but the amount of ore they can bring in is pretty small.  Higher level players can set up mining operations in aster
oid fields and manage them in a Real Time Strategy format, keeping mining drones busy, shipping the ore to space stations, and defending themselves against pirates and enemy factions.  The {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Union{\*\xmlclose}
 is particularly adept at mining practices, but the Colonials, with their speed, and the Federation with their technology can also participate in mining operations.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\ul\insrsid6230726 A Universe Defined By Player Actions
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6230726 The ability to affect the persistent online Universe is a feature often touted by almost every MMORPG, but in 
practice we find that players have a rather limited effect on their own.  Teams of Players (sometimes called \'93Guilds\'94, in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \ul\insrsid6230726 The Fringe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6230726 , they are called 
\'93Wing Groups\'94, \'93Battle Groups\'94, and \'93Carrier Groups\'94) might be able to stage a raid on Player and Non-Player controlled regions, but their effects are temporary.  In }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \ul\insrsid6230726 The Fringe}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6230726 , regions of space that are captured by an enemy faction are maintained by that faction.  Players can go online and see a live update of the political structure of the universe, and how 
their recent battles online have played a role.  Battles will have historical significance and players will be able to read about (and brag about) battles that they actually participated in.  \'93I commanded a destroyer in the \lquote 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Battle{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} of the Belt\rquote .\'94
  This over-riding game of universal conquest is directed by real high-level players (some professional), that will give orders to those other players that have played enough to become Carrier Group Admirals, who will then pass on their commands through t
he command structure in a real-time game of galactic \'93Risk.\'94
\par 
\par As the Fringe Universe expands, we expect the story development to reflect the universe players have changed the game into. Some uber-rich player with a massive ship and big guns could find thems
elves in the story, with NPC quests to hunt him!  As groups of players complete tasks outside their normal quest-line, we might tie the story around events that could happen, such as if a pirate raid attacks a station, reinforcements could be set so they 
c
ould run out, and possibly the station could be lost. If the station is lost, the story would then be forced to tie around it. If the station isn't, the pirate raid, if inflicting enough damage, would become well known across Camorah, and the station itse
lf would have to recover from damages.
\par 
\par One thing about story lines is that everyone loves them, but no one wants to take the time to read them.  We plan on producing an episodic show (at first web-cast, but you never know what might happen later) that tell
s the story, and stays up to date with what is really happening in the Fringe Universe.  Players that are in to writing can include histories of the battles from their own carrier groups and these carrier groups will have their own stories to tell with th
eir own web sites.  Some of these stories can be submitted and included with the major game story line.  This episodic show will serve to be a marketing tool and possibly an additional revenue stream.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\ul\insrsid6230726 Tiered Combat Command Structure
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6230726 As we see the results o
f combat have more far reaching effects, the battles become more complex.  Each class of ship is made to depend on the other ships in its Carrier Group.  A fighter, for instance, has a very specific role within a combat, and would be at a huge disadvantag
e if alone, regardless of the player\rquote s skill.
\par 
\par Successful battles will be waged with a great deal of strategy in mind.  Players will have the opportunity to not only control capital ships, but be able to command the assets (player controlled and non-player 
controlled) of that capital ship in a real-time-strategy style.  Carrier Group Admirals, for instance, will have a far-reaching tactical map of the entire conflict, including entire planetary systems, and will be able to direct actions to Battleships, Des
troyers, Fighter Wings, etc.  These command vessels will not have the big picture of the battle, but will need to depend on their admirals and carry out their commands with exactness, or risk being destroyed in an un-coordinated attack.  The player
\rquote s rank a
nd status also depend on how well he is able to carry out commands.  As before, these individual battle groups pass orders down to smaller support vessels and fighter ships.  Fighter pilots will have a very narrow view of the battle around them, and will 
need to depend on their command hierarchy for instructions, refueling, rearming, and targeting information.
